    "name": "Sobol global sensitivity analysis — non-cannulated pedicle screw FEA QoIs",
    "description": "A variance-based Sobol sensitivity analysis (N=2048 quasi-random Saltelli samples, total N_eval=20480) was performed across eight uncertain inputs: Ti-6Al-4V Young's modulus, yield strength, rod-to-screw interface friction coefficient, screw root fillet radius (±0.02 mm manufacturing tolerance), polyaxial head engagement angle, cortical bone surrogate modulus (UHMWPE block per F1717), crosshead displacement rate, and interbody spacer height. First-order and total-effect Sobol indices were computed for three QoIs: construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement. Dominant first-order contributors were Ti-6Al-4V Young's modulus (S1=0.41 for stiffness), rod-to-screw friction coefficient (S1=0.28 for yield force), and screw root fillet radius (S1=0.33 for force at 40 mm displacement); total-effect indices confirmed negligible higher-order interactions (ST–S1 < 0.05 for all factors). Results informed the UQ budget allocation and confirmed that mesh refinement uncertainty is subordinate to material property uncertainty for all three QoIs.",
    "method": "Variance-based Sobol decomposition (Saltelli quasi-random sampling)",
